This paper is most likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with video super-resolution using convolutional neural networks. It may also belong to Multimedia (cs.MM) as it deals with video processing. Additionally, it may belong to Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it uses neural networks for prediction. It may also belong to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with enhancing the quality of video frames. Finally, it may belong to Graphics (cs.GR) as it deals with improving the visual quality of videos.
